author: DJ Alpha Omega
text: We both came from broken homes, abusive pasts, & held secrets we never shared with the rest of the world, but we always overcame the odds against us & succeeded in achieving so much. We never shared so much with anyone else & feelings of not only love but a connection that would never leave was something we both never realized would ever happen in such a grand way. I still think about those moments we shared, the love we have, & I see you when you look at my socials thinking I don't notice you as you check in on me. We are both living very different lives, such success came at a price. Even with the way things are, I wouldn't have traded anything for it, but I would trade it all for you, A.P.

author: MechaGodJovi
text:
I still need to finish this game. I've played it back when it released as FF3 in 1994 but this is the only game in the series I've never completed. I've tried to finish it on multiple occasions since and got to the end once then just stopped, no clue why. 

The game wasn't too hard or boring but I always picked a bad time to play it and get distracted by new releases every time I'd get into it. I also find it hard to go back to a save on an RPG if I haven't touched the game for over a month and always felt like I needed to restart to get a refresher of the story lol...maybe one day.

author: dorgrim
text: Junior in high school.  Rented Final Fantasy 3 from Blockbuster.  Played it and beat it after several rentals, hoping my saved game would still be there next weekend.  I loved FInal Fantasy 1 on NES, beat it, then played Final Fantasy 2 on SNES.  Beat it.  But what I didn't know is I would play and beat FF3 yearly for 26 years.  Back then that's what we knew them by, not 4 and 6.
